# Phase 4 — Reinforcement Learning Auto-Optimizer

## Overview

Phase 4 adds a **prescriptive AI layer** on top of Phases 1–3. Where Phase 2 answers *"what will happen?"* and Phase 3 answers *"what happens if X changes?"*, Phase 4 answers **"what should we do right now?"**

A PPO (Proximal Policy Optimization) agent learns to **reallocate agents across queues** to minimize SLA breaches and maximize throughput — fully without Kafka/Redis for standalone training, with an optional inference module that writes recommendations to the FeatureStore.

---

## How It Integrates with Previous Phases

```
Phase 1 (Kafka Features)
        ↓
Phase 2 (LSTM / XGBoost breach predictions)
        ↓
Phase 3 (SimPy simulation → breach rates per scenario)   ← RL trains IN THIS environment
        ↓
Phase 4 (PPO agent → optimal agent reallocation actions)
        ↓
FeatureStore (rl:recommendations:latest) → Phase 5 Dashboard
```

The RL environment wraps the Phase 3 `QueueSimulation` engine: **each RL step = one simulated 8-hour shift**. The agent observes queue states and chooses how to move agents; the simulator returns the resulting breach rate as the reward signal.

