## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Choice | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| RL algorithm | PPO (stable-baselines3) | Battle-tested, works well on low-dimensional continuous control, easy to tune |
| Sim runs per step | 10 averaged | Reduces stochasticity in reward signal; fast enough (~0.1s/step) |
| Action space | MultiDiscrete([5]×6) | Simpler than full combinatorial; agent learns per-queue independently |
| Observation space | 48-dim Box (6 queues × 8 features) | Compact; covers all operationally relevant state |
| Budget constraint | Total agents ±3 from baseline | Prevents trivially overstaffing all queues |
| Curriculum | 3-phase (easy→hard) | Prevents early convergence to suboptimal "do nothing" policy |
| Training time | ~200k steps ≈ 5–10 min | Fast enough for local machine; visible progress |

